> This crowd-pleasing pizza-style fondue is a fun, delicious way to gather family and friends around the table! You'll combine crispy browned chicken sausage and tangy marinara with Italian cheeses in a creamy base, top with a shower of mozzarella, and pop it all in the oven until bubbly for a show-stopping presentation. Serve family style with veggies and toasty bread for dunking—don't mind if we fon-due!

> This recipe is double the typical servings, providing 4 servings and 8 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a  #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{18%oz} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Stir in @marinara{7.5%oz cup}; cook, stirring, until sauce is hot and sausage is coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add a splash of water.

Remove from heat, cover, and set aside until ready to use in Step 5.

While sausage cooks, wash and dry produce. Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, core, and slice @bell pepper{2} into 1-inch strips.

Halve @flatbreads{2} lengthwise, then cut each half crosswise into 1-inch strips. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and @pepper{}; toast on top rack until browned, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove from oven; let cool completely.

While flatbreads bake, heat @cream sauce base{8%oz} and @cheese roux concentrate{1%oz} in a #small pot{} (use a #medium pot{} for 8 servings) over medium-high heat until steaming and slightly bubbling, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium. Add @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup} and half the @mozzarella cheese{1%cup} one small handful at a time, alternating and whisking constantly between additions until fully melted.

Transfer fondue to an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (use a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{} for 8 servings); top with sausage sauce and remaining mozzarella.

Once you've removed flatbreads from oven, turn on broiler. Broil pizza fun-due, uncovered, until cheese on top is melted and browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning!

Arrange broccoli, bell peppers, and flatbreads on a #large board{} or #platter{}. Serve with pizza fun-due for dipping and @chili flakes{1%tsp} on the side.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.